/nA tailor uses basic, bland materials to craft unique and stunning clothes. Equally adept with scissors, needle, or thread, good tailors can make complex garments with astounding alacrity. /n/nIt's amazing how much more suave, striking, or deadly the right tailor can make someone look./n/n Housing Type: Tailor Shop

/nA blacksmith works metal to make weapons, armor, shields, and even books. Blacksmiths never smile as broadly as when sweat is pouring from their brows and their cheeks are smudged with soot, hammering on anvils and pumping at bellows./n/nBlacksmiths can make adventurers stronger, safer, and more imposing./n/n Housing Type: Smithy

/nA chef makes delectable meals that transform ordinary ingredients into extraordinary taste experiences. Theirs is a constant balancing act, balancing taste and texture, sweet and savory, spice and mild./n/nDishes prepared by the most talented chefs can even grant special powers or weaken enemies. n/n/ Housing Type: Restaurant

/nBalancing offense and defense, the battle-style of warriors varies greatly, from those who prefer delicate work with sword and shield to those more fond of shattering skulls with two-handed warhammers./n/nWarriors stand firm in a fight, refusing to back down while protecting weaker party members.

/nThieves are quick and stealthy, dealing powerful melee damage enemies never see coming. They also employ ranged attacks and are masters of camouflage./n/nInvaluable in any party, a talented thief can weaken enemies' spirits as much as their bodies.

/nMages call upon arcane and eldritch forces to aid them as they attack from a distance. Burning, drowning, and even burying enemies with elemental magicks are all common skills in a mage's repertoire./n/nThe mere sight of a powerful mage has caused many an enemy to quake in fear...no magic necessary.

/nClerics truly care about the well-being of their comrades, performing a variety of healing skills to protect the injured…and sometimes raise the fallen./n/nReliably dedicated, clerics are the noblest of souls, constantly defending the sanctity of life itself.

/nThe Muris inhabit a floating island off East Orta; its very air dances with magic. This petite race revels in the luxuries of life - from the chilly thrill of bathing in the starlight to the rush of sipping gourmet teas. /nHowever, the Muris have been known to baffle the other races of Orta - particularly the Turga - because their insular existence means they know next to nothing about the world. Still, they've heard enough legends about the mainland to bravely open their island to historians and adventurers searching for Lime. /nEventually, some Muris even joined the hunt for Lime, hoping to make their secret wishes come true./n/nAvailable Battle Classes: Warrior, Thief, Mage
